@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem
Summary
  An item representing a graphic object.
Description
  TJvPreviewGraphicItem is the class of items maintained by the TJvPreviewGraphicItems class. It
  represents the image data and property settings for a graphic object that can be rendered to
  a preview.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.Center
Summary
  Specifies if the graphic should be centered in it's container.
Description
  Use Center to specify whether the image should be centered on the preview page or not.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.DestRect
Summary
  Calculates the size of the output rectangle based on a reference rectangle and a DC.
Description
  Call DestRect to calculate the size of the output rectangle needed fo he image when it is resized
  according to the settings of the DC.
Parameters
  RefRect - Reference rectangle.
  DestDC  - The DC to render to.
Return value
  A rectangle that specifies the coordinates of the required destination rectangle of the image.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.Picture
Summary
  The graphic object associated with this item.
Description
  Use Picture to specify the image that is associated with this object. At design time, click the
  ellipsis button in the Object Inspector to select an image.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.Proportional
Summary
  Indicates whether the image should be changed, without distortion, so that it fits the bounds of
  the container.
Description
  Use Proportional to set whether images are stretched to fill the entire client area when Stretch is true
  or if they should be stretched to fill as much as possible without changing the original width to height
  ratio of the image.
See Also
  DestRect, Stretch
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.Stretch
Summary
  Indicates whether the image should be changed so that it exactly fits the bounds of the container.
Description
  If Stretch is true, the image is changed to fill the entire available client area. If Stretch is false,
  the image is displayed at it's original size.
See Also
  Proportional
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.Transparent
Summary
  Indicates whether the image should be rendered transparently.
Description
  Use Transparent to indicate whether the background of the rendering area is filled or not.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItem.UpdateGraphic
Summary
  Updates the image to match the current property settings.
Description
  Call UpdateGraphic to make sure that property changes are propagated to the image in Picture.
See Also
  Picture
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItems
Summary
  Collection that maintains a list of graphic objects.
Description
  TJvPreviewGraphicItems is a collection that maintains a list of TJvPreviewGraphicItem objects.
  TJvPreviewGraphicItems is the type of the <LINK TJvPreviewRenderGraphics.Items, Items> property of
  TJvPreviewRenderGraphics.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItems.Add
Summary
  Adds a new graphic object to the collection.
Description
  Call add to add a new image object to the collection.
Return value
  The newly added image object.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewGraphicItems.Items
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the items in the collection.
Description
  Use Items to access the image objects using an index.
