@@TJvPreviewPrinter
<TITLEIMG TJvPreviewPrinter>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Miscel
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A class that implements the IJvPrinter interface using TPrinter as the output device.
Description
  Use TJvPreviewPrinter when you want to output the content of a preview control to the printer.
  If a preview control is assigned to the PrintPreview property, calling Print will
  call the preview control's <LINK TJvCustomPreviewControl.PrintRange, PrintRange>
  method to create a printout using the current settings of the TJvPreviewPrinter
  and send it to the currently selected printer.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Assign
Summary
  Copies the properties of a compatible object to this object
Description
  Call Assign to copy the properties of a TJvPreviewPrinter or a TPrintDialog to this object.
  If Source is a TPrintDialog the Collate, Copies, FromPage, Options, PrintRange and ToPage
  properties are copied.
Parameters
  Source - The object to copy from
See Also
  TPrintDialog, Collate, Copies, FromPage, Options, PrintRange, ToPage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Collate
Summary
  Indicates whether collating is active.
Description
  Use Collate to specify if collating should be used or not when printing.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Copies
Summary
  Indicates the number of copies to print.
Description
  Set Copies to the number of copies of the document to print. Copies can never be less than 1.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.FromPage
Summary
  Indicates the page on which the print job is to begin.
Description
  The FromPage property corresponds to the From field in a Print dialog.
See Also
  ToPage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnAbort
Summary
  Occurs when the print job is aborted.
Description
  Write a handler for OnAbort to take specific action when the print job is aborted. For example,
  you could display a dialog to the user warning them that the print job was aborted or you could
  hide a progress dialog previously shown in OnBeginDoc.
See Also
  OnBeginDoc, OnEndDoc, OnNewPage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnBeginDoc
Summary
  Occurs when the print job is started.
Description
  Write a handler for OnBeginDoc to take specific action when the print job starts. For example, you
  could display a dialog to the user while the printing is in progress.
See Also
  OnNewPage, OnEndDoc
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnEndDoc
Summary
  Occurs when the print job is finished.
Description
  Write a handler for OnEndDoc to take specific action when the print job has finished. For example,
  you could hide a dialog previously shown in OnBeginDoc.
See Also
  OnBeginDoc, OnNewPage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnNewPage
Summary
  Occurs when a new page is to be printed.
Description
  Write a handler for OnNewPage to take specific action when a new page is about to be sent to the printer.
  For example, you can update the progress on a dialog shown to the user.
Parameters
  Sender    - The object that called the event.
  PageIndex - The number of the page that is to be printed.
See Also
  OnBeginDoc, OnEndDoc, OnAbort
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Options
Summary
  Indicates the options to use when a print dialog is displayed.
Description
  Use Options to specify the print options to use when a print dialog is to be displayed. Options
  isn't used by TJvPreviewPrinter itself. It is only provided as a convenient way of storing the
  print dialog options without actually having to create a dialog to house them.
See Also
  TPrintDialog.Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Print
Summary
  Starts the print job.
Description
  Call Print to send the document in the preview control to the printer. If a preview control is
  assigned to the PrintPreview property, it's PrintRange method is called to do the actual printing. 
See Also
  PrintPreview
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Printer
Summary
  Provides access to the global printer object.
Description
  \Read Printer to access the properties and methods of the TPrinter class.
See Also
  TPrinter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.PrintPreview
Summary
  Specifies the print preview control that is responsible for creating the print job.
Description
  Set PrintPreview to a TJvCustomPreviewControl or descendant that should be handling the
  creation of the document to print. TJvPreviewPrinter does not itself provide methods for creating
  the document. Instead, it uses the <LINK TJvCustomPreviewControl.PrintRange, PrintRange> method
  of TJvCustomPreviewControl to do the actual work.
See Also
  TJvCustomPreviewControl
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.PrintRange
Summary
  Specifies whether FromPage and ToPage are valid.
Description
  Use PrintRange to determine whether FromPage and ToPage contains valid values. If PrintRange
  is prAllPages, FromPage and ToPage are ignored, otherwise they are considered valid.
Note
  prSelection is not supported by the print preview components at his time.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Title
Summary
  Determines the text that is listed in the Print Manager and on network header pages.
Description
  Title is used by Windows in the Print Manager and for network title pages.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.ToPage
Summary
  Indicates the page on which the print job is to end.
Description
  The ToPage property corresponds to the To field in a Print dialog.
See Also
  FromPage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl
<TITLEIMG TJvPreviewRenderControl>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Miscel
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Renders a preview of a TControl descendant.
Description
  Use TJvPreviewRenderControl when you want to render a TControl descendant (visual control) in a simple
  way. Assign the TControl to render to the Control property and call the CreatePreview method to render
  the output to a preview control.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Center
Summary
  Indicates whether the preview is centered in it's container.
Description
  Use Center to specify whether the TControl is rendered centered on the preview control
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Control
Summary
  Indicates the control to render.
Description
  Use Control to specify the TControl descendant to render to the preview control. If Control is nil,
  no preview is generated when CreatePreview is called.
See Also
  CreatePreview
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Proportional
Summary
  Indicates whether the Control preview should be changed, without distortion, so that it fits the
  bounds of the container.
Description
  Use Proportional to set whether the Control preview is stretched to fill the entire client area
  or if it should be stretched to fill as much as possible without changing the original width to height
  ratio of the image. Proportional only have effect if Stretch is true.
See Also
  TJvPreviewGraphicItem.DestRect, Stretch
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Stretch
Summary
  Indicates whether the Control preview should be changed so that it exactly fits the bounds of
  the container.
Description
  If Stretch is true, the image is changed to fill the entire available client area. If Stretch is false,
  the image is displayed at it's original size.
See Also
  Proportional
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderGraphics
<TITLEIMG TJvPreviewRenderGraphics>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Miscel
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A renderer that can render a collection of images.
Description
  Use TJvPreviewRenderGraphics when you want to preview a set of images. Add images to the renderer
  by using the methods of the Images property. Every image in the collection can have a different format
  and use different property settings. When you are ready to show the preview, call CreatePreview.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderGraphics.Images
Summary
  A collection of images to render.
Description
  Use Images to add and modify the images to preview. At design time, click the ellipsis button
  in the Object Inspector to show the collection editor. Use the editor to add and modify
  the images in the collection.
See Also
  CreatePreview
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderRichEdit
<TITLEIMG TJvPreviewRenderRichEdit>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Miscel
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Preview renderer for rich edits.
Description
  Use TJvPreviewRenderRichEdit when you want to render a preview of the content in a rich edit control.
  This renderer supports formatted output of RTF. Assign a rich edit to the RichEdit property and call
  CreatePreview to render the rich edit to a preview control.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderRichEdit.RichEdit
Summary
  References the rich edit that should be rendered.
Description
  Set RichEdit to a rich edit control on your form that you want to preview.
See Also
  CreatePreview
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderStrings
<TITLEIMG TJvPreviewRenderStrings>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Miscel
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Preview render for string lists.
Description
  Use TJvPreviewRenderStrings when you want to render a preview for a TStrings or descendant. Assign
  a TStrings to the Strings property or use the methods of Strings to add content to the string list.
  Use Font to specify the visual appearance of the text and call CreatePreview to render the string list
  content to a print preview control.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderStrings.Font
Summary
  Specifies the font settings to use in when rendering.
Description
  Use Font to specify the font settings to use when creating the preview. Changing the properties
  of the font won't be instantly visible in the preview. Call CreatePreview to update the preview.
See Also
  CreatePreview
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderStrings.Strings
Summary
  List of text strings that should be rendered.
Description
  use Strings to specify the text strings to render to the preview. You can copy strings from any other
  control or TStrings descendant by assigning directly to the Strings property or you can use
  the methods of TStrings (like Add, Remove, LoadFromFile etc) to define the content of the list.

  To view the new or changed content of Strings, you must call the CreatePreview method.
See Also
  CreatePreview
